# 000 — Global Rules

- This is a TypeScript-strict monorepo. No JavaScript files except config roots.
- Architecture is strictly modular and layered, with a one-directional dependency rule.
- No direct LLM calls anywhere except `packages/llm-gateway`.
- No `eval`, no `new Function`, no dynamic code execution.
- All runtime features must have tests.
- No shortcuts: no `as any`, no `// @ts-ignore`, no skipped tests.
- Commit messages follow Conventional Commits.
- Every structuring decision must have an ADR in `docs/adr/`.
- **Mandatory human review**: any very important change (architecture, runtime invariants, public package APIs, security, large rewrites/deletions) must be proposed first, then reviewed and explicitly validated by the maintainers before being applied. Never apply such a change on your own initiative.